    <briefdescription>
<para>Contains a design example using the <ref refid="struct_x_dp" kindref="compound">XDp</ref> driver (operating in TX mode) with polling. </para>    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para>Once the polling detects a Hot-Plug-Detect event (HPD - DisplayPort cable is plugged/unplugged or the monitor is turned on/off), the main link will be trained.</para><para><simplesect kind="note"><para>For this example to display output, the user will need to implement initialization of the system (Dptx_PlatformInit) and, after training is complete, implement configuration of the video stream source in order to provide the DisplayPort core with input (Dptx_StreamSrc* - called in <ref refid="xdp__tx__example__common_8c" kindref="compound">xdp_tx_example_common.c</ref>). See XAPP1178 for reference. </para><simplesectsep/><para>The functions Dptx_PlatformInit and Dptx_StreamSrc* are declared extern in <ref refid="xdp__tx__example__common_8h" kindref="compound">xdp_tx_example_common.h</ref> and are left up to the user to implement.</para></simplesect>
<preformatted>
MODIFICATION HISTORY:</preformatted></para><para><preformatted>Ver   Who  Date     Changes
<hruler/>

1.0   als  01/20/15 Initial creation.
5.1   ms   01/23/17 Added xil_printf statement in main function to
                    ensure that &quot;Successfully ran&quot; and &quot;Failed&quot; strings
                    are available in all examples. This is a fix for
                    CR-965028.
</preformatted> </para>    </detaileddescription>
